				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="Smart Four Connected" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>Offers two games.  A three dimensional four-in-a-row game that you can play against a human opponent or against 3 levels of AI or Lights Out, a game played solely against one of 3 levels of AI in which your goal is to turn off all the lit up spaces.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The four-in-a-row game, known as Smart Four, is similar to other four-in-a-row games, with a couple of differences.  First, the four in a row can happen in any dimensions, so four blocks stacked atop of each other would be a win.  The other is that the electronic board will confirm when a winning move has been played by flashing when a victory has been achieved.  This can be played versus a human player or against 3 levels of AI.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In the other game, Lights Out, played solely against one of three levels of AI, is one in which the goal is to shut all the lit up spots on the board off.  Depending on the difficulty level, some number of spots will be lit up.  When a player presses a spot on the board, all orthogonally adjacent spots will switch from off to on or on to off depending on their original state.  A player wins when all lights are out.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
